  "prompt": "Does a user always need to keep the data \u2018ON\u2019 for outgoing/incoming calls on Jio network?",
  "response": "On the Jio network, users do not always need to keep mobile data 'ON' for calls. Jio uses Voice over LTE (VoLTE) technology, which allows voice calls to be made using the 4G data network. However, here are some important points:\n\n1. For VoLTE calls:\n- Data should be turned ON\n- Requires a 4G VoLTE-compatible phone\n- Provides better call quality\n\n2. For regular voice calls:\n- Data can be turned OFF\n- Works like traditional cellular calls\n- Supported on most phones\n\n3. Exceptions:\n- Video calls typically require data to be ON\n- Wi-Fi calling might need data connectivity\n\n4. Best practice:\n- Keep data ON for seamless calling experience\n- Ensures better call connectivity and quality\n\nSo while data is recommended, it's not absolutely mandatory for making basic voice calls on the Jio network.",
